 <title>Earning people&#039;s trust every day</title>
 <link>http://www.watchmn.org/online-newsletters/summer-2011/earning-peoples-trust-every-day</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; by Marna Anderson, Executive Director&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In the mid-1990s, I lived in rural El Salvador and worked with a nongovernmental organization. The civil war had ended. Law enforcement was no longer controlled by the military, but local police departments were nonexistent in many parts of the country. The closest precinct to my community was approximately 15 kilometers away—a 45-minute drive due to poor road conditions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.watchmn.org/online-newsletters/summer-2011/earning-peoples-trust-every-day&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
