<item>
 <title>UN report urges justice system reform and monitoring to increase women&#039;s access and participation</title>
 <link>http://www.watchmn.org/online-newsletters/summer-2011/un-report-urges-justice-system-reform-and-monitoring-increase-womens-</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;UN Women was launched in February as an umbrella agency of the United Nations, consolidating several agencies into one to address global women’s issues. Its first report, Progress of the World’s Women in Pursuit of Justice, released July 6, points to the ongoing problems facing women worldwide seeking justice through the courts. It cites complicated legal processes, long delays, and mounting financial and social costs as key reasons many women abandon their attempts to achieve justice through the legal system.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.watchmn.org/online-newsletters/summer-2011/un-report-urges-justice-system-reform-and-monitoring-increase-womens-&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
